N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1 ยง 23.1 - Eligible producer

State Regulations

For the purposes of the Dairy Assistance Program
established pursuant to Agriculture and Markets Law, section 258-p p, eligible
producer means a New York State producer who was in operation on April 1, 2007
and who produced milk during the 2006 calendar year. Notes
